WEBVTT

00:00.959 --> 00:03.962
♪♪

00:31.656 --> 00:33.616
Mornin'.

00:33.616 --> 00:35.618
Hi, Bobby.

00:42.584 --> 00:45.628
You got me through.

00:45.628 --> 00:47.964
I'm glad you showed up.

00:53.011 --> 00:55.013
Now I know what it was.

00:58.058 --> 01:00.810
You'll get yourself
some help.

01:00.810 --> 01:02.812
Yeah.

01:08.109 --> 01:10.779
No one deserved waiting
how you had to, Bobby.

01:10.779 --> 01:13.656
No one deserves
a lot that happens.

01:16.701 --> 01:19.245
When Mary was sick,

01:19.245 --> 01:21.164
I couldn't help her.

01:23.625 --> 01:26.002
I'm glad enough
I was able to help you.

01:34.052 --> 01:36.137
Here I am.

01:47.315 --> 01:50.318
♪♪

03:08.146 --> 03:10.732
-Andy, I need
to talk with you.
-You'll get over it.

03:10.732 --> 03:12.984
Please. I know
about something bad.

03:12.984 --> 03:16.696
And I've heard all I'm
listening to about body juices
and rubber corsets.

03:16.696 --> 03:20.783
-A death. A dead man.
-What do you
know about that?

03:20.783 --> 03:23.578
He's a friend,
and I stopped by his
apartment this morning,

03:23.578 --> 03:26.331
-and he was hanging.
-Hanging?

03:26.331 --> 03:29.834
-How'd you come
to stop by?
-He's a friend.

03:29.834 --> 03:34.130
I'm wondering, were you
worried about him, how you
happened to stop by?

03:35.924 --> 03:39.969
-Andy, we got a homicide
over at a construction site.
Hey, Geri.

03:42.430 --> 03:45.058
D.O.A. off a fight at
a construction site, James.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.644
-Couple of coalitions
were involved.
-Okay.

03:47.644 --> 03:50.521
Hey, boss.
Geri just told me,

03:50.521 --> 03:53.191
uh, a friend of hers
is dead at his apartment.

03:53.191 --> 03:57.820
She found him hanging.
I don't know if you want her to
ride over there with somebody.

03:57.820 --> 04:01.616
-No, I'm not going back there.
-I'd like you to talk to
Det. Kirkendall and Russell.

04:01.616 --> 04:04.285
Give 'em what information
you have so they can
take a look at it.

04:04.285 --> 04:06.621
I'd rather give it
to Detective Sipowicz.

04:06.621 --> 04:09.707
No. Kirkendall and Russell's
how we're gonna do it.

04:12.835 --> 04:14.545
All right.

04:18.132 --> 04:20.677
-Construction coalition, huh?
-Mm-hmm.

04:20.677 --> 04:23.596
There's a solid bunch
of citizens.

04:25.473 --> 04:28.476
Diane, Jill.

04:28.476 --> 04:31.437
Uh, Geri found a friend of
hers dead in his apartment.

04:31.437 --> 04:34.440
-Um, can you talk
to her about it?
-Sure.

04:34.440 --> 04:37.235
Don't put me
through this like a suspect,
all right, Lieutenant?

04:37.235 --> 04:39.654
No one is treating you
like a suspect, Geri.

04:39.654 --> 04:43.658
Antagonize me
like you have before,
and I won't cooperate.

04:43.658 --> 04:47.245
I understand.

04:47.245 --> 04:48.871
Geri, is your friend
there now?

04:48.871 --> 04:51.666
His name is Tom Konigsberg,
and that's all I know about it.

04:51.666 --> 04:55.003
If you give us Tom's address,
Diane and I can get over there.

04:55.003 --> 04:58.298
(chuckles)
You're gonna
have a real good time
with me, aren't you?

04:58.298 --> 05:00.717
Find him hanging.

05:00.717 --> 05:04.012
Why don't you just write
the address for us, Geri?
Come on.

05:08.391 --> 05:10.977
Gonna have a real
day at the beach.

05:14.647 --> 05:17.650
♪♪

05:41.758 --> 05:44.761
Freeze a furry tit,
I'm out with one glove on.

05:44.761 --> 05:47.555
Theo likes to sleep on it.
He thinks it's like
some teddy bear.

05:47.555 --> 05:49.349
-He was on it
this morning, huh?
-Yeah.

05:49.349 --> 05:52.977
Look, Andy. I'm sorry I didn't
spend more time on the phone
with you last night.

05:52.977 --> 05:55.313
-I was relieved you called.
-Diane, she was
all stirred up.

05:55.313 --> 05:57.523
I didn't want to be
away from her too long.

05:57.523 --> 06:00.735
She, uh, got things
off her chest.
She's got things, you know.

06:00.735 --> 06:03.946
-I'm just hoping
she'll feel better now.
-She looks better this morning.

06:03.946 --> 06:07.033
Yeah, I'm optimistic.

06:08.159 --> 06:09.744
What happened?

06:09.744 --> 06:11.746
Two coalitions
went at it.
One D.O.A.,

06:11.746 --> 06:14.957
-four at the hospital,
the rest are cuffed.
-You see any of it?

06:14.957 --> 06:17.752
Black coalition shows up.
Name's None Forgotten.

06:17.752 --> 06:19.754
Start twisting arms
for jobs.

06:19.754 --> 06:21.798
Few minutes later,
here comes Bronx United.

06:21.798 --> 06:24.217
-Which is Puerto Rican.
-Right.

06:24.217 --> 06:27.011
Construction boss calls us
'cause he sees what's coming.

06:27.011 --> 06:29.597
By the time we get here,
the shape directors are
already into it.

06:29.597 --> 06:32.016
There's six or seven
set-tos all around the yard.

06:32.016 --> 06:36.396
-Anybody see this guy get hit?
-Too busy swinging hammers,
tossing bricks.

06:36.979 --> 06:38.648
Got a wallet.

06:40.316 --> 06:43.569
Emilio Lopez,
Shape Director, Bronx United.

06:43.569 --> 06:46.364
Bulletproof vest.
Looks like Emilio figured...

06:46.364 --> 06:48.366
that he'd have a pretty
bad day in front of him.

06:48.366 --> 06:52.370
-We got six guns.
-Yeah, assorted pipes,
hammers, bats.

06:52.370 --> 06:54.789
Donnybrook's like
a daily thing with these guys.

06:54.789 --> 06:57.375
-Bunch of phony hustlers.
-How's it
make it phonies,

06:57.375 --> 07:00.211
trying to persuade
these site bosses to
give jobs to minorities?

07:00.211 --> 07:02.797
They're phonies
'cause their big
persuasion techniques...

07:02.797 --> 07:04.841
is knocking people
around with ball bats,

07:04.841 --> 07:06.843
and their preferred
job position--

07:06.843 --> 07:09.053
they don't actually have to
show up to do no work.

07:09.053 --> 07:11.055
Not one honest guy
in the bunch, right, Andy?

07:11.055 --> 07:13.850
Maybe I'm wrong, Martinez.
Maybe one of
these good folks...

07:13.850 --> 07:17.270
is gonna leap up
and say he saw
a murder committed.

07:17.270 --> 07:19.814
Listen, we're gonna need
transpo to get all these guys
back to the house.

07:19.814 --> 07:22.024
-They need to be
interviewed.
-Sure.

07:22.024 --> 07:24.026
All right.

07:25.820 --> 07:28.030
-Andy's missing a glove.
-Yeah.

07:28.030 --> 07:31.242
That accounts for his, uh,
piss-poor attitude, right?

07:31.242 --> 07:34.245
That, and he don't
like most people.

07:38.291 --> 07:41.294
♪♪

07:45.673 --> 07:48.092
-Morning.
-How's it going?

07:48.092 --> 07:51.471
Well, 911 took
an anonymous call, said
someone hung theirselves.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.890
-M.E.'s on the way.
Landlady's downstairs.
-Can you get her?

07:53.890 --> 07:57.143
-Yeah, sure.
-Thanks.

08:14.076 --> 08:16.078
Planned on
going to work today.

08:16.078 --> 08:18.080
That's why this towel's
around the rope.

08:18.080 --> 08:20.374
He didn't want ligature marks.

08:30.510 --> 08:33.846
Oh, this is
just flabbergasting.

08:34.722 --> 08:38.935
-I'm Diane Russell.
This is Detective Kirkendall.
-Millie Holden.

08:38.935 --> 08:41.479
Millie, can you
I.D. this man?

08:41.479 --> 08:45.942
Tom Konigsberg.
He's lived here
a year and a half.

08:45.942 --> 08:48.110
What can you
tell us about him?

08:48.110 --> 08:51.489
Well, I had no inkling
of this carrying-on.

08:51.489 --> 08:54.909
He worked steady.
He was a punctual rent-payer.

08:54.909 --> 09:00.122
Believe me, I never saw him
in dresses or any inkling
of this contraption.

09:00.122 --> 09:02.500
He never even
played loud music.

09:02.500 --> 09:04.710
Did anyone else have
a key to his apartment?

09:04.710 --> 09:09.173
A girlfriend, I think.
She stayed here one or two
times a week.

09:09.173 --> 09:13.553
Uh, her name was Geri.
Uh, she's, uh,
chunky build,

09:13.553 --> 09:16.389
um, low to middle
30 years of age.

09:16.389 --> 09:18.766
-Uh, Geri Turner.
-Good.

09:18.766 --> 09:20.768
She had brownish-red hair,

09:20.768 --> 09:24.730
-and she was
5'8" to 5'10".
-Uh-huh.

09:24.730 --> 09:26.732
Do you think
she did this to him?

09:26.732 --> 09:29.360
-We're gonna have to
look into that.
-Thanks very much for your help.

09:29.360 --> 09:32.947
-Oh, listen, I don't have to
tell the family, do I?
-No. No, we'll take care of
that.

09:32.947 --> 09:36.158
If it was my son,
I'd want someone should
lie to me how they found him.

09:36.158 --> 09:37.368
Thank you.

09:39.954 --> 09:42.540
(sighs)
Maybe we ought to check
at the sex store,

09:42.540 --> 09:44.959
see if they remember
this guy with anybody but Geri.

09:44.959 --> 09:48.546
So you're really not looking
forward to going back to the
house to interview Geri, huh?

09:48.546 --> 09:50.506
You got that right.

09:59.140 --> 10:02.226
Slap me for saying
those boots look kinda cool.

10:11.652 --> 10:14.572
(chattering)

10:14.572 --> 10:16.407
You guys, sit right there.

10:19.785 --> 10:23.998
D.O.A. took one in the head.
Name's Emilio Lopez. He's the
number two guy for Bronx United.

10:23.998 --> 10:25.750
Comes to work with
a bulletproof vest.

10:25.750 --> 10:29.003
We got six ditched weapons,
but it's gonna be tough
to get the prints.

10:29.003 --> 10:31.255
Yeah, this cold,
everybody's wearing gloves.

10:31.255 --> 10:34.842
Half these guys got sheets,
plus they're in factions
against each other.

10:34.842 --> 10:38.262
Who gets the most snouts
in the trough for no-show jobs.

10:38.262 --> 10:40.264
That's the contractor
over there. We're gonna
start with him.

10:40.264 --> 10:42.642
You notify
the D.O.A.'s family?

10:42.642 --> 10:46.812
She was taking the kids
to school. We left a message
with the neighbors.

10:46.812 --> 10:48.022
-Yeah.
-Yo, can I get out of here?

10:48.022 --> 10:50.232
-Keep me posted.
-What's your name?

10:50.232 --> 10:54.028
-Ray Harvey.
-Where were you standing when
the shootin' happened, Ray?

10:54.028 --> 10:56.030
I don't know.
That's why I want to get out.

10:56.030 --> 10:58.824
-You don't know where
you were standing?
-Uh-uh.

10:58.824 --> 11:03.037
-Did you hear the shots?
-Had my Walkman on. That's what
I'm trying to tell you all.

11:03.037 --> 11:05.623
-Where is it you gotta be?
-Gotta take my sister
to the doctor.

11:05.623 --> 11:08.250
-What if you had a job to go to?
-She wouldn't get to go.

11:08.250 --> 11:11.045
-Can you be back here at 4:00?
-Yeah, I can be
back here by then.

11:11.045 --> 11:14.298
All right. Write your name,
address and home phone.

11:14.298 --> 11:16.717
Got any picture I.D.,
Mr. Harvey?

11:19.428 --> 11:22.098
Some coffee, Mr. Deluca?

11:22.098 --> 11:24.100
I'm nervous enough
as it is.

11:24.100 --> 11:26.310
-Decaf?
-No.

11:26.310 --> 11:28.854
Really something
that went on today, huh?

11:28.854 --> 11:32.066
I go through crap with
these coalitions all the time.

11:32.066 --> 11:35.861
They show up, no tools,
no skills worth a crap.

11:35.861 --> 11:38.656
I don't hire them,
the site goes up for grabs.

11:38.656 --> 11:42.868
I put up with
the B.S., the brawls.

11:43.285 --> 11:45.663
But a killing?

11:45.663 --> 11:47.289
You know Emilio Lopez?

11:47.289 --> 11:50.876
No. I talked to him
for, like, two seconds
this morning.

11:50.876 --> 11:52.670
Then Bluestone
got in his face.

11:52.670 --> 11:55.548
Bluestone being from
this other coalition,
None Forgotten?

11:55.548 --> 11:58.926
-The black group, right.
-Did Bluestone have
a weapon that you saw...

11:58.926 --> 12:00.344
when he was
in Lopez's face?

12:00.344 --> 12:04.932
-I don't know.
I went to my office.
-You went to your office.

12:04.932 --> 12:07.935
Look, all I wanted was to
put up this senior center...

12:07.935 --> 12:10.104
without
the sky falling in.

12:10.104 --> 12:13.441
I put up with everything,
and still something
worse still happens.

12:21.240 --> 12:23.325
All right, I'm gonna
say something here.

12:23.325 --> 12:25.703
And probably it's gonna get
my head beat or something else.

12:25.703 --> 12:29.331
I'm gonna say I have
a tape here which is
a surveillance tape of the site.

12:29.331 --> 12:32.543
Maybe you people will see
something in conjunction
with your investigation...

12:32.543 --> 12:34.712
to show
who did what.

12:34.712 --> 12:37.965
And if that happens,
all I'm asking is...

12:37.965 --> 12:40.760
not to be quoted
the source of that tape.

12:40.760 --> 12:44.013
But I'm going this far
because this is murder.

12:46.223 --> 12:50.186
And enough's enough.

12:50.186 --> 12:53.564
WOMAN:
Oh, my God! Oh, no!
(crying)

12:53.564 --> 12:54.648
Stick right here.

12:54.648 --> 12:57.359
Oh, my God!
No, Emilio!
(speaking Spanish)

12:57.359 --> 13:01.739
Why don't you sit here
with James, Mrs. Lopez.
I'll get you some water.

13:01.739 --> 13:04.742
-Oh, my God!
-Shh. Take it easy, all right?

13:04.742 --> 13:07.578
Who did it?
Who killed Emilio?

13:07.578 --> 13:09.371
We're looking into
how it happened.

13:09.371 --> 13:11.165
He was an honest man.

13:11.165 --> 13:13.375
He believed
what he was doing.
He was good.

13:13.375 --> 13:14.960
Sir, you can't
go in there.

13:14.960 --> 13:17.588
Dina! Dina! Dina.
(Spanish)

13:17.588 --> 13:20.633
No! No. No.
Who killed Emilio?

13:20.633 --> 13:24.428
I swear, we're gonna find
that out. I'm Joe Fernandez,
head of Bronx United.

13:24.428 --> 13:28.224
-You weren't at the site?
-We've been tied up at the
office ever since the shooting.

13:28.224 --> 13:31.018
-Phone's been ringing
like there's no tomorrow.
MAN:Hey, Jose.

13:31.018 --> 13:33.771
Hermanos.
(Spanish)

13:33.771 --> 13:37.191
My husband was an honest man,
and he's dead for trying
to do good.

13:37.191 --> 13:41.403
-That's right, Dina.
-He was honest. He was
trying to get real jobs.

13:41.403 --> 13:44.406
-You let it out, mijita.
You let it out.
-Hey, hey. Hey.

13:44.406 --> 13:45.783
-Over here.
-Absolutely.

13:45.783 --> 13:48.619
-You take good care
of her, you hear?
-Talk a walk.

13:48.619 --> 13:51.789
-And we had
three little kids.
-Try and take it easy.

13:51.789 --> 13:54.416
What am I gonna do?
My God!

13:54.416 --> 13:58.003
So, maybe a decent guy
got through the net into one
of these groups, huh, Andy?

13:58.003 --> 14:01.298
Yeah, and maybe it
got him killed.

14:14.395 --> 14:17.356
♪♪

14:32.288 --> 14:36.250
-Ladies.
-Detectives.
15th Squad.

14:36.250 --> 14:37.084
Oh.

14:37.084 --> 14:39.795
We're investigating
an incident involving
one of your customers.

14:39.795 --> 14:43.090
He recently bought
a pair of leather cuffs
here at your shop.

14:43.090 --> 14:46.510
We sell an array of restraints.
You'll have to be more specific.

14:46.510 --> 14:48.929
Black leather
wrist and ankle restraints.

14:48.929 --> 14:51.181
Silver spiked collar
connected by chains.

14:51.181 --> 14:53.434
-Uh-huh.
-Ring a bell?

14:53.434 --> 14:56.937
Those could be our
Beast-Master cuffs.

15:07.489 --> 15:09.950
Right.
Those are the ones.

15:12.411 --> 15:14.079
Do you recognize him?

15:14.079 --> 15:16.874
-Do I legally have to say?
-What's your name?

15:16.874 --> 15:20.294
-Lori Gittman.
-We're investigating
a felony, Lori.

15:20.294 --> 15:23.964
You withhold information,
you're obstructing,
which is a felony too.

15:25.549 --> 15:27.843
Okay.
So I recognize him.

15:27.843 --> 15:29.929
What about people he'd
frequent the shop with?

15:29.929 --> 15:33.307
-Got any pictures?
-No.

15:33.307 --> 15:36.560
There's this heavy woman,
um, with dark red hair.

15:36.560 --> 15:40.522
Usually came in with him.
Bought a lot of
dominatrix stuff.

15:40.522 --> 15:43.984
And some pretty ballsy
lingerie for a woman of
her proportion.

15:45.235 --> 15:46.904
-Did she die?
-No.

15:46.904 --> 15:50.908
-He's not with us anymore.
-Uh-oh.

15:50.908 --> 15:54.328
Do you remember anyone
other than the heavyset
woman being with him?

15:54.328 --> 15:57.122
He'd come in by himself
sometimes, but when
he was with someone else,

15:57.122 --> 16:00.042
it was always
with her.

16:00.042 --> 16:01.126
-Okay. Thanks a lot.
-Okay.

16:01.126 --> 16:03.671
I think her name was Geri.

16:05.798 --> 16:07.007
Great.

16:11.428 --> 16:14.431
♪♪

16:16.141 --> 16:18.686
Have a seat, Mr. Fernandez.

16:26.568 --> 16:30.322
This here's a $1,200 suit.
You want me to sit in
someone's coffee cake crumbs?

16:30.322 --> 16:32.574
Maid's day off.

16:32.574 --> 16:34.952
Hold my men, keep us all
from a day's pay.

16:34.952 --> 16:37.579
Look at it
like a mourning period
for Emilio Lopez.

16:37.579 --> 16:39.748
Emilio was solid
with the coalition.

16:39.748 --> 16:41.792
Would've wanted us
we kept keeping on.

16:41.792 --> 16:44.962
Both coalition officers,
you and him
must've been tight?

16:44.962 --> 16:47.006
-Sure.
-Or not.

16:47.006 --> 16:49.174
Don't speak bad of the dead.

16:49.174 --> 16:53.637
-Suppose he was still around?
-Then probably be running
his mouth, preaching.

16:53.637 --> 16:56.056
Aren't the coalitions for
the workers to speak up?

16:56.056 --> 17:00.227
That's the political side,
what Lopez did.
I did the business part--

17:00.227 --> 17:02.187
getting people work,
food on the table.

17:02.187 --> 17:05.482
-You tell me what's better.
-How about the no-show jobs
and shakedowns?

17:05.482 --> 17:08.193
-How'd Lopez feel
about those?
-Don't take your meaning.

17:08.193 --> 17:10.988
Site bosses tighten you up
to keep trouble out.

17:10.988 --> 17:14.408
Emilio want a piece
of that money, Joe?

17:14.408 --> 17:16.201
I wasn't even
at the site, all right?

17:16.201 --> 17:18.370
Is that a yes on wanting
some of your action, Joe?

17:18.370 --> 17:22.291
Emilio wasn't down
for lining his pockets.
Big man of the people.

17:22.291 --> 17:25.210
Lopez mention to you
he was starting
his own coalition?

17:25.210 --> 17:27.421
I heard some of that talk.
Then from there...

17:27.421 --> 17:30.257
he was gonna stand up
for the community,
then city politics.

17:30.257 --> 17:32.259
Then next,
Herman Badillo.

17:32.259 --> 17:35.262
Nothing worse than a guy
with dreams, huh, Joe?

17:35.262 --> 17:37.681
Didn't like him,
and I didn't kill him.

17:37.681 --> 17:41.060
Wasn't at the site.

17:41.060 --> 17:42.686
-(sighs)
-Maybe you two got
a hard-on for me...

17:42.686 --> 17:45.939
'cause I make six figures
and don't even have
a high school diploma.

17:45.939 --> 17:48.442
That it?

17:48.442 --> 17:50.569
Bye, Fernandez.
Let's go.

18:00.579 --> 18:03.749
There.
Uh, the shooting
was at 7:20, right?

18:03.749 --> 18:06.043
Yeah.

18:06.043 --> 18:08.337
You need some batteries
in here, Lieu.

18:16.178 --> 18:20.099
Uh-huh. That's the tube steak's
head of the None Forgotten.

18:20.099 --> 18:24.937
-Bluestone.
-Yeah. Puts a bat
in his hand, but no gun.

18:24.937 --> 18:28.607
Main fighting's on the right.
This guy's coming from
the opposite direction.

18:28.607 --> 18:32.694
Isn't that that Ray Harvey guy
that Greg and James were
talking to here in the squad?

18:33.487 --> 18:35.948
Ready to make arrests?

18:38.075 --> 18:41.912
Maybe behind Bluestone
showing no piece,
you rule him out as a suspect.

18:41.912 --> 18:44.498
Look to him for a push
who he thinks did it.

18:44.498 --> 18:47.501
Sister Sun Ray--
says she's got something
for you on this.

18:47.501 --> 18:48.919
