I'm not pretty.

34:27.648 --> 34:32.111
And he seemed to like that
'cause he was really shy.

34:34.238 --> 34:37.658
But then he got
into it so much that he
didn't even look at me.

34:37.658 --> 34:43.539
He wanted to be
blindfolded and have,
like, private orgasms.

34:43.664 --> 34:45.958
And it broke my heart.

35:01.099 --> 35:03.810
Did you kill him, Geri?

35:04.393 --> 35:08.815
I was just in there crying,
and he started without me,

35:10.483 --> 35:14.153
which he was doing
more and more.

35:16.948 --> 35:19.158
He didn't
like me anymore.

35:20.952 --> 35:22.411
He told me
six weeks ago...

35:22.411 --> 35:27.083
that he was
having other people in
to dominate him too.

35:29.502 --> 35:33.131
I started
trying to be friendly
to you after that...

35:33.131 --> 35:35.133
because you're blustery,

35:35.133 --> 35:38.594
but in your heart,
I think you take people
as you find them.

35:41.764 --> 35:44.559
And I thought maybe...

35:44.559 --> 35:46.519
you could have
a crush on me.

35:49.647 --> 35:51.524
The way you want to put
your statement, Geri,

35:51.524 --> 35:53.734
so they realize
you were innocent...

35:53.734 --> 35:57.113
is no tears or "he begun
seeing other people,"

35:57.113 --> 36:00.741
let the D.A. start
looking at jealousy
or so forth.

36:00.741 --> 36:04.328
You both liked
playing these games.

36:04.328 --> 36:06.747
You were his spotter.
While you were in the crapper,

36:06.747 --> 36:09.750
he jumps the gun,
you come out,
you find Tom dead.

36:09.750 --> 36:12.128
End of story.

36:16.382 --> 36:18.593
Sorry for your loss.

36:37.945 --> 36:40.948
♪♪

36:48.789 --> 36:50.166
Come back
like I said, right?

36:50.166 --> 36:53.169
Yeah, you kept
your word good, Ray.

36:53.169 --> 36:56.422
That's Detectives Simone
and Sipowicz. Guys,
this is Ray Harvey.

36:56.422 --> 36:59.467
-How's it going?
-O-Okay.

37:02.720 --> 37:07.642
So, uh--So, I told you,
uh, this morning...

37:07.642 --> 37:11.312
I was present at that
incident, but I wasn't,
like, no witness.

37:11.312 --> 37:13.022
They just want to go over
the sequence with you.

37:13.022 --> 37:15.024
I don't know
no sequence 'cause I didn't
see what went down.

37:15.024 --> 37:18.027
So, we got that
established now.
Okay, Ray?

37:18.027 --> 37:21.197
-Your position is
you don't know nothing?
-Exactly.

37:21.197 --> 37:24.825
So how 'bout you listening to
what we know, so we can all stop
running through the grease here.

37:24.825 --> 37:28.204
What's he talking about?
I showed back up here
on my own cause.

37:28.204 --> 37:31.207
You showed back up, Ray,
'cause you didn't figure
your friends...

37:31.207 --> 37:35.211
Sam and Madam Sunflower Seed
to put you in the middle
of this, right?

37:35.211 --> 37:38.256
But that shows you
that life can be
full of surprises.

37:38.256 --> 37:40.675
I think that's Sister Sun Ray.

37:40.675 --> 37:45.096
The fat, black broad you hit
the number with, Ray, then you
ask her advice like Dean Witter?

37:45.096 --> 37:47.473
Hit the number
turned into a crime now?

37:47.473 --> 37:49.267
Huh? Four detectives?!

37:49.267 --> 37:53.437
Sister Sun Ray gave you up for
killing Emilio Lopez, Ray.

37:53.437 --> 37:55.982
She said you killed him
protecting your loan
to his boss.

37:55.982 --> 37:57.650
Hey. Hey. What you
coming at me with?

37:57.650 --> 38:00.861
And Sam Bluestone,
your other bosom pal?

38:00.861 --> 38:02.446
He backs the Sister too.

38:02.446 --> 38:05.866
-The both of 'em put you
whacking this guy.
-Hey, hey, hey. This is sick.

38:05.866 --> 38:08.452
See, now the question that
occurs to us here, Ray,

38:08.452 --> 38:13.249
is being how this story
more or less got laid to us
all nice and neat--

38:13.249 --> 38:16.168
maybe you got a competing
version on how this man died.

38:22.133 --> 38:23.134
I got nothing to say.

38:23.134 --> 38:25.928
Nothing to say?
Present circumstances, Ray,

38:25.928 --> 38:29.932
that translates,
"Let me bend over
and spread 'em real wide."

38:29.932 --> 38:32.310
Are those people
framing you,
Sister Sun Ray and Sam?

38:32.310 --> 38:34.937
-I'm not guilty!
-So they are framing you.

38:34.937 --> 38:37.106
Tell 'em I never
figured 'em to do me
like this.

38:37.106 --> 38:39.692
That's what you want us
to tell 'em, Ray?
How 'bout we tell them,

38:39.692 --> 38:42.903
"I ain't being your patsy
no more. I'm saying what
really went down here."

38:42.903 --> 38:45.906
You should put them in there
with me. They should
get jacked up too.

38:45.906 --> 38:48.909
-How would that work?
-Were they in on this
with you, Ray?

38:48.909 --> 38:53.706
Set me up from the jump.
Sister and Sam okay this guy
for me making the loan.

38:53.706 --> 38:56.917
-Next thing I know,
he ain't paying dick.
-This is Joe Fernandez.

38:56.917 --> 39:00.379
Now they all agitated.
Joe Fernandez short...

39:00.379 --> 39:03.341
'cause Lopez taking
his action away
behind that coalition.

39:03.341 --> 39:06.344
I wanna look out
for my money I loaned.

39:06.344 --> 39:08.763
Lopez keep Fernandez
from paying.

39:08.763 --> 39:10.765
Did they tell you
to kill this guy?

39:10.765 --> 39:12.767
I was at the Sister's
last night.

39:12.767 --> 39:16.187
Sam come by saying Lopez
be at the site tomorrow
shaping for jobs.

39:16.187 --> 39:18.522
-Did they tell you to kill him?
-I was drunk!

39:18.522 --> 39:21.317
They had me half-crazy.

39:21.317 --> 39:24.862
Wound him up like
the Energizer Bunny.

39:25.946 --> 39:30.951
Ray, did Bluestone
give you the gun?
Or the Sister?

39:30.951 --> 39:34.330
'Cause they tied you
like a Christmas package.

39:34.330 --> 39:36.457
You ought to
return the favor.

39:39.960 --> 39:43.214
-My gun.
-You sure you don't
wanna lie about that?

39:43.214 --> 39:47.218
I swear to God I wish
I'd never won that money.

39:47.218 --> 39:51.055
Brought me nothing
but worry and misery.

40:00.147 --> 40:04.777
The perfect frame.
Makes me sick.

40:04.777 --> 40:06.987
You think there was
some other reason they
wanted this Lopez dead...

40:06.987 --> 40:09.365
past him queering
their union hustles?

40:09.365 --> 40:14.578
Who knows? Maybe they
break out in hives being
around an honest man.

40:14.578 --> 40:17.581
Such an easy patsy, though,
this poor dope Harvey.

40:17.581 --> 40:20.793
I knew this bookmaker,
John Riley.

40:20.793 --> 40:23.587
When somebody won big,
John'd make a big fuss
paying 'em off.

40:23.587 --> 40:27.842
Give him a good cigar,
next day's racing form.
He'd say to me afterwards,

40:27.842 --> 40:30.052
"I'm just letting 'em
hold the money a while."

40:30.052 --> 40:32.054
Yeah, that's
the Sister and Ray.

40:32.054 --> 40:34.849
It really used to
piss me off. It's like
it wasn't a fair fight.

40:34.849 --> 40:37.184
Not like how it
is usually, huh?

40:37.184 --> 40:38.185
Yeah.

40:38.185 --> 40:40.813
I'll tell you,
I'm in for justice here.
So, you just trust me.

40:40.813 --> 40:44.233
-It's one of them.
-Well, look who's a little
more speechifyin'.

40:44.233 --> 40:46.235
You got a None Forgotten
in custody?

40:46.235 --> 40:48.821
Who told you, Joe?
Your bed pals,
Sam and the Sister?

40:48.821 --> 40:51.824
People gonna know how Emilio
died at a black man's hand.

40:51.824 --> 40:55.035
There's gonna be employment
for boricuas or blood
will run at the sites.

40:55.035 --> 40:57.830
Joe's gonna go to
the papers with this
phony race homicide,

40:57.830 --> 41:00.040
try to scare up
some more no-show jobs.

41:00.040 --> 41:02.626
Hypocrite bastard.
You're like
Monday Night Wrestling.

41:02.626 --> 41:07.673
Let me tell you something, Joe.
When you take this to the
papers, you know what you're
gonna do?

41:07.673 --> 41:10.676
-You're gonna be pledging
some money to Lopez's widow.
-That's already in the works.

41:10.676 --> 41:14.221
Well, that's good 'cause
you're gonna draw a contract up
with one of our D.A.'s here,

41:14.221 --> 41:16.974
-a trust for his
widow and children.
-Already in the works.

41:16.974 --> 41:21.103
You're gonna write it
here, Joe. So it's all nice
and legal and binding...

41:21.103 --> 41:23.063
before you walk out,
or this whole thing
is going...

41:23.063 --> 41:26.108
to the D.A.'s office
on a conspiracy charge.

41:29.653 --> 41:31.655
I'm happy to make
that commitment.

41:31.655 --> 41:35.451
-Great.
-Let me hunt up a wonderful
attorney acquaintance of ours.

41:35.451 --> 41:41.165
A Leo Cohen. Why don't you
sit down there, Joe.
Go on. Have a seat.

41:45.669 --> 41:48.547
How's it going with you?

41:50.424 --> 41:54.720
I was, um--
I was wondering about
your after work plans.

41:54.720 --> 41:56.722
There's nothing on my calendar.

41:56.722 --> 42:02.728
Hmm. And, uh,
would that be for
the foreseeable future?

42:02.728 --> 42:07.691
How is that
they say in your program?
One day at a time.

42:07.691 --> 42:09.902
I can do it that way.

42:09.902 --> 42:13.322
Leo?
Andy Sipowicz. Yeah.

42:13.322 --> 42:16.909
Could you, uh, just trot on
upstairs here for a moment?

42:16.909 --> 42:19.703
Yeah. Thank you.
(handset settles in cradle)

42:19.703 --> 42:21.664
He's on his way up.

42:21.664 --> 42:24.667
♪♪

42:34.552 --> 42:37.179
-Boy, that was
just great.
-Thanks, James.

42:37.179 --> 42:40.558
Really. Yeah. Your mom
teach you your cooking?

42:40.558 --> 42:42.393
My mom and my aunt.

42:42.393 --> 42:44.937
I really enjoy spending
this time with you, Gina.

42:44.937 --> 42:47.565
I could get into being
a man of leisure.

42:51.068 --> 42:55.281
I really appreciated it.
Just as far as, um--

42:57.366 --> 43:00.536
You know, she changed
her commitment.
She's not coming back.

43:00.536 --> 43:02.955
This is your roommate?

43:02.955 --> 43:06.917
Said she made
another arrangement
for the new semester.

43:07.126 --> 43:10.379
She's gonna be
picking up her stuff.

43:10.379 --> 43:14.008
-I've been upset on that.
-Financially?

43:14.008 --> 43:16.010
Financially and--

43:16.010 --> 43:20.222
I know she was upset
about my appearance.
It disturbed her.

43:20.222 --> 43:23.809
-That's baloney.
-No, she said so, James.

43:23.809 --> 43:26.562
Well, the heck with her!
That's nonsense.

43:26.562 --> 43:28.772
And financially,
you're coming back
to work.

43:28.772 --> 43:31.567
If you need some tiding over,
that's no problem at all.

43:31.567 --> 43:35.571
That's not necessary.
I got my confirmation savings.

43:35.571 --> 43:38.782
It's mostly you being here.
It's helped me a lot.

43:38.782 --> 43:40.868
It's my pleasure.

43:43.662 --> 43:47.625
Anyways, I know you got
an 8:00-to-4:00.

43:50.878 --> 43:53.255
Don't take this
as being forward,

43:53.255 --> 43:56.842
but if you wanted some
company tonight, I could stay up
in your roommate's loft there.

43:56.842 --> 43:59.637
If you'd like to stay,
I'd be happy for you to.

43:59.637 --> 44:02.640
I'd like to.
Sure.

44:02.640 --> 44:05.059
But if you
sleep up in her loft,
I'd worry all night...

44:05.059 --> 44:07.853
that you'd sit up
in a strange place
and smash your head.

44:07.853 --> 44:11.190
Yeah. I suppose that
could occur. Sure.

44:13.525 --> 44:16.028
And as far as me
sleeping up there,

44:16.028 --> 44:19.448
I could always fib and say
I'm afraid of heights.

44:19.448 --> 44:22.242
You don't gotta fib.

44:22.242 --> 44:25.037
We could both stay in there.

44:26.038 --> 44:29.166
That's where I was
hoping we'd come out.

44:43.180 --> 44:46.183
♪♪
